messages.content: "You don’t understand me at all."
Nash spreads his hands, still bleeding from his mouth. “Enlighten me! What am I *fucking* missing!”
"I didn’t say I was planning on changing that." She grabs his shirt collar. "Come on, let’s go get your mother."
“To.. to deal with this?”

"Sure. Come on." Ruth.

"Is it… Over?" Orion says nervously.
Nash bites down on his bottom lip hard enough to bleed.
Ruth drags Nash down the staircase.
Nash follows hopelessly.
Orion trails behind them.
Nash continues to allow himself to be pulled along.

They arrive at the Duchess’s home. Oswalda and Washington are talking in the entrance.

"Hello, Nash." Oswalda.
“H-hello.” *Don’t fucking stammer, you coward.*

"Nash, have you seen the duchess?" Washington.

"That’s what we were here to ask you, actually." Ruth casually lets Nash go like nothing happened.

"Have *none* of you seen the Duchess all day? I suppose she could still be in her room. That’s odd, though…" Oswalda.
Nash blinks. “I… haven’t, no.”

"Her room?" Washington rushes off in that direction anxiously.

Ruth eyes him suspiciously and follows.

Nash follows too.

*She’s fine. She’s a busy woman. She has things to attend to, as usual. Nothing to worry about.*
Orion follows.

The Duchess’s bedroom is a large fancy looking library with only slight accommodations to fit the role of a bedroom. She has a bed, a nightstand, and a work desk. The rest of the room is occupied by as many books as possible, with shelves hugging the walls or positioned in the center of the room that act like walls. She is not here.
“Well.” Nash says dismissively. “She must be busy with work. This happens fairly often.”

"If she were busy with work she’d be here or meeting with *someone*." Washington starts tossing books around vaguely looking for something.

"What’s going on…?" Kori enters the room.
“Hold on!” Nash takes a step forwards. “What gives you the right to rummage through her stuff..?”
He ignores Nash.
“Hey!” Nash yells. He steps closer to Washington, bristling with anger.

"Naaaash? What's going on?" Kori.

Washington keeps ignoring Nash.
“Don’t ignore me!” Nash snaps. He shoves Washington.
((Roll strength))

Washington isn't moved in the slightest.

Several people rush into the room, including Aeolian.
They arrive at the Duchess’s home. Oswalda, the maid, welcomes them. "Hello?"
“Hello.”

"Where is the duchess? We need to speak with her immediately." Aliza.

"Oh, you’re looking for her too? Your father just went up to see her." Oswalda.
“That’s not good.”

"Why not? Is something wrong?" Oswalda.

"Please take us there, she could be in danger." Aliza.

"Oh? Very well…" Oswalda heads into the house looking confused.
I follow.
Several people are in the Duchess's bedroom, including Nash Edwardson.
All of these people and Aeolian and Nash are in the room.

The Duchess’s bedroom is a large fancy looking library with only slight accommodations to fit the role of a bedroom. She has a bed, a nightstand, and a work desk. The rest of the room is occupied by as many books as possible, with shelves hugging the walls or positioned in the center of the room that act like walls. She is not here.
"W-what? What are you doing here?" Nash says, extremely frustrated. "All of you, just get out!"
“Ah. She isn’t here.” I shrug. “I suppose that’s for the best, then.”
Nash grips at his hair, looking somewhat frenzied. "Ahhh.. why can't you people just leave my family alone?!?" He tries to shove Washington again.
“It’s likely related to their high relevance to national political affairs.”
"You shut up!"
“No.”
“No.”

"Aliza...? What are you doing here?" Washington stares at her nervously.

"Father, you have to stop!" Aliza takes out her rapier. "I won't let you kill the duchess." 

"Tch. So that's how it's going to play out, is it...?" Washington.

"Wait- Kill the Duchess? What?" Archer guy.

Ruth gets into a fighting stance. "I knew there was something wrong with this guy." 

"Everyone, please calm down! Wh- What's going on!?" Oswalda.

"Can you all just kill each other already?" Child. ((Roll initiative))

Washington casts Spiritual Weapon to summon a spectral greatsword that swings onto Aeolian's green-haired companion for 9 damage. Then he punches Aeolian for 5 damage. For his movement he jumps up into the air and clings to the top of the nearest bookshelf, pulling himself 3ft in the air. 

It's @Aeolian Burr's turn.
"Get out of here, Aliza! I don't want to hurt you!" Washington.
“Ow.” I cast sanctuary on Aliza. “Did you kill the emperor, Washington?”

"Ally, I'm the only person here who doesn't need sanctuary!" Aliza.

Sanctuary is a bonus action, do you want to do anything else?
“I’m not entirely sure what anyone is doing here.” I take out my dagger but don’t do anything with it. “This seems endlessly less productive than simply discussing what our intents are.”

"You always were a moron, Burr." Washington.

"I've got him, Nash." The archer hits Washington with an arrow. 

It's @Nash Edwardson's turn.
Nash tries to fucking stab Washington with his longsword.
((What's the reach?))
((Roll as normal then))
((21 to hit))
It hits.
((8 for damage))

Kori watches this without doing anything.

"How lucky for the duchess that she's raised nothing but psychopaths!" Washington.

"Do not speak of her children that way!" Oswalda swings a morningstar at Washington but misses.

"Tch. It wasn't you I was trying to piss off." Washington.

Aliza stabs her father's foot. "Please just give up!"

Green haired guy tries to break the bookshelf itself. This fails.

Ruth leaps onto the bookshelf and attempts to grapple him. He slips out with ease.

Washington tosses a glass container of water and casts control water, causing it to explode outward towards everyone. ((Roll a dex save))

Ruth avoids this entirely by being in the air. Nash, Kori, Oswalda, and Aliza all avoid the water. Aeolian, the archer, and the green haired guy are all knocked prone. 

Washington's spectral blade strikes the archer with advantage.

It's Aeolian's turn.
I get up.

The archer stands up. 

It's Nash's turn.
Nash tries to stab Washington again. He's trying to hurt her. He's trying to hurt mom. He needs to be taken apart. He needs to be...
((21 to hit))
It hits.
((8 for damage))

This shatters his concentration, ending the control water spell.

Kori still doesn't do anything except watch.

Oswalda attempts to swing her morningstar at Washington, but misses and hits Ruth. The pain causes Ruth to slip and fall onto Oswalda and knock them both prone.

"M-My apologies, but please get off me..." Oswalda.

"You hit me, bitch!" Ruth.

Aliza stabs her father once again. "You're not going to win this, father! Just let us arrest you."

Green haired guy gets up.

Ruth gets up.

Washington casts Spirit Guardians at 4th level.((Wisdom saves for anyone not within 15 feet of Washington. The people who were pushed away by the water and haven't come back(Like Aeolian) aren't in the zone))
((Also your speed is halved in the zone but this isn't an issue in this room))

Angelic spirits shoot out from around Washington and swarm those around him, except Aliza. Nash, Ruth, and Oswalda fail the save. Kori makes the save. Aliza is completely spared from the spell. It deals 13 damage to those who fail and half that to those who make it. Kori is knocked below 0hp.

Despite the advantage, his weapon fails to hit Oswalda.

It's Aeolian's turn.
((can i do non-combat actions during not-my-turn))
((No. The only things you can do out of turn are talk and drop concentration on a spell))
((weh))
"Kori!" Nash yells. Is she.. unconscious?
I attempt to get closer to Washington and then hit him with my dagger.
The spirit guardians swarm Aeolian as he enters the zone. ((Do a wisdom save))
I am incredibly wise.

Aeolian takes 20 damage and crumples to the ground.

The archer's arrow misses completely.  "Fuck!"

It's Nash's turn. He's starting in the zone so he would normally have to do another wisdom save. ((I misread the spell so to rebalance this I won't hurt you with the spell on this turn you were only supposed to take damage on your turn whoops))
((ok so i just take 13 points of dmg in total or?))
((Yeah))
Nash is bleeding heavily from the mouth now. He foregoes doing anything else in order to rush over to Kori's side in a panic. Is she okay?
She’s unconscious and not stable.

"Ah... aaaah......" Why did he never learn any fucking healing spells? Is he stupid? Why can't he fix her? He thought it would be... like, indicative of something, about him, for him to learn, so he never.. he never.. is this the consequence?? That he could never, care for her properly. Because he was without the necessary tools, the framework, to fuckin'... achieve that! Aughhh, idiot, fucking moron, stop self-flagellating over what's gotten you here in the first place and fix it! Fix it! Fix it! Can't you fix it! You're supposed to be able to soothe anything that's wrong, you, you, stupid shit, you...
He picks up her limp body and tries to run out of the room with it.
((You can stabilize her for note that is an action you can take that requires a medicine roll))
Fuck. Alright. He'll try that.
Kori is stabilized.
"Ghh.. ghh..." He still wants her out of here. He still tries to leave with her.

"Wait! Keep her out of the spell, but stay close. I can heal everyone." Aliza.

Kori is still unconscious.

Oswalda gets up. 

Aliza fails to stab her father.

The green haired rushes in and stabs Washington, breaking his concentration finally and ending the spell. "I did it, Lord Burr!"

Ruth tries to grab him again, but he instead uses her as a platform to jump up onto the top of the bookshelf. He is now 10 feet in the air. "Slippery piece of shit!"

Washington casts control water once again, causing the water to expand exponentially once again.

((Nash roll a dex save. Aeolian roll a death save))

The archer, the green haired man, and Aliza are knocked prone. Nash, Ruth, and Oswalda avoid the surging water which has reached the level of their ankles.

Nash is hit for 7 damage by the spectral sword. "I'm not going to let you go and warn your mother, Nash."
Nash has reached 0 HP.
